  "prompt": "How do you know if you have a crush on someone?",
  "response": "Having a crush on someone typically involves a mix of emotional and physical responses. Here are some common signs that might indicate you have a crush on someone:\n\n1. **Excitement and Nervousness**: You feel excited when you see or think about the person, sometimes accompanied by butterflies in your stomach.\n\n2. **Preoccupation**: You find yourself thinking about the person frequently, even when you're supposed to be focused on other things.\n\n3. **Desire to Spend Time Together**: You look forward to opportunities to hang out with the person and may feel disappointed when plans don't work out.\n\n4. **Attention to Appearance**: You become more conscious of your appearance and may put extra effort into looking your best when you know you'll be around them.\n\n5. **Interest in Their Life**: You feel genuinely curious about and interested in their opinions, hobbies, and experiences.\n\n6. **Daydreaming**: You daydream about scenarios involving the person, imagining how great it would be to spend time together or have them acknowledge your feelings.\n\n7. **Jealousy**: You might feel a pang of jealousy when you see them interacting closely with others.\n\n8. **Physical Responses**: Your heart races, or you blush when you interact with them or even think about them.\n\n9. **Nervous Flutters**: You become unusually nervous or shy when talking to them, sometimes stumbling over your words.\n\n10. **Heightened Sensitivity**: You might notice or remember small details about them that others overlook, like the way they laugh or their favorite color.\n\nIf you identify with several of these signs, it could be a strong indication that you have a crush on someone.",
